法規內容.條文內容:
No fishing vessel shall conduct the following operations in a foreign base without prior authorization:
1. Use the foreign base for the purposes of fishing, selling of fish, or taking supplies;
2. Use the foreign base for the purposes of transshipping fish products.

With respect to the national crews he hired, a fishery operator of a fishing vessel which intend to operate in a foreign base, shall:
1. Submit the name list of crewmembers to the coastal guard authority of the port of its registration;
2. Inform the district fishermen’s association where the vessel belongs for record, in case of change of the crewmembers;
3. Have the crewmember repatriated to his home, in case any crewmember leaves the fishing vessel at a foreign base.
The crewmembers of any fishing vessel authorized to operate in a foreign base shall not leave port until security inspection has been conducted by the coastal guard authority at the port of its registration.
